		body: "### Command\r\n\r\nbuild\r\n\r\n### Is this a regression?\r\n\r\n- [X] Yes, this behavior used to work in the previous version\r\n\r\n### The previous version in which this bug was not present was\r\n\r\nv15\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen I run an `ng build` with source maps turned on, I can't read them with `source-map-explorer` (source-map-explorer@2.5.3).\r\n\r\nSeems like the generated source map may be invalid?\r\n\r\n### Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit clone github.com/stephenfluin/baby-log/\r\ncd baby-log\r\nyarn\r\nng build\r\n```\r\nINstall source-map-explorer wherever you want (`yarn global add source-map-explorer`)\r\n\r\nsource-map-explorer dist/baby-log/src_app_home_home_module_ts.js\r\n\r\n### Exception or Error\r\n\r\n```text\r\nsrc_app_home_home_module_ts.js\r\n  Your source map refers to generated line 23, but the source only contains 19 line(s).\r\n  Check that you are using the correct source map.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Your Environment\r\n\r\n```text\r\nAngular CLI: 16.0.0\r\nNode: 16.14.2\r\nPackage Manager: yarn 1.22.19\r\nOS: linux x64\r\n\r\nAngular: 16.0.0\r\n... animations, cdk, cli, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core\r\n... forms, language-service, localize, material\r\n... platform-browser, platform-browser-dynamic, router\r\n\r\nPackage                         Version\r\n---------------------------------------------------------\r\n@angular-devkit/architect       0.1600.0\r\n@angular-devkit/build-angular   16.0.0\r\n@angular-devkit/core            16.0.0\r\n@angular-devkit/schematics      15.2.8\r\n@angular/fire                   7.5.0\r\n@schematics/angular             16.0.0\r\nrxjs                            7.8.1\r\ntypescript                      5.0.4\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Anything else relevant?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
